.TH MC-INSTALLER 1 "December 2025" "mc-installer 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mc-installer \- Minecraft Launcher installer for Fedora Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mc-installer
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-\-force\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mc-installer
is a simple installer for the Minecraft launcher on Fedora Linux.
It performs a per-user installation without requiring root privileges.
.PP
The installer downloads the official Minecraft launcher from Mojang,
extracts it to the user's home directory, and creates desktop integration
files for easy access from the application menu.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message and installation paths
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information including Git commit and build date
.TP
.BR \-\-force
Force reinstallation even if Minecraft launcher is already installed
.SH INSTALLATION LOCATIONS
The installer uses standard XDG Base Directory locations:
.TP
.I ~/opt/minecraft-launcher/
Main application directory containing the Minecraft launcher executable
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/applications/minecraft.desktop
Desktop entry file for application menu integration
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/icons/minecraft.png
Application icon
.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
No root/sudo required (per-user installation)
.IP \(bu 2
Automatic download from Mojang's official source
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop integration with application menu
.IP \(bu 2
Mesa workaround for Fedora compatibility
.IP \(bu 2
Idempotent installation (skips completed steps)
.IP \(bu 2
Self-contained binary with embedded resources
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Install Minecraft launcher:
.B mc-installer
.TP
Show version information:
.B mc-installer \-\-version
.TP
Force reinstallation:
.B mc-installer \-\-force
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/opt/minecraft-launcher/minecraft-launcher
Main Minecraft launcher executable
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/applications/minecraft.desktop
Desktop entry file
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/icons/minecraft.png
Application icon
.TP
.I /tmp/minecraft-launcher.tar.gz
Temporary download file (automatically cleaned up)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B __GLX_VENDOR_LIBRARY_NAME
Set to "mesa" when launching Minecraft for Fedora compatibility
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful installation or help/version display
.TP
.B 1
Installation error (permission denied, download failed, etc.)
.SH UNINSTALLATION
To remove Minecraft launcher:
.PP
.nf
.RS
rm -rf ~/opt/minecraft-launcher
rm ~/.local/share/applications/minecraft.desktop
rm ~/.local/share/icons/minecraft.png
.RE
.fi
